Durban - Officials from the KwaZulu-Natal Department of Education today paid a visit to a number of schools as hundreds of pupils sat to write their English exam. 
Speaking at the visit, the MEC said they are hoping that no schools in the province will have zero pass rates. 

MEC Mthandeni Dlungwane noted that there were three schools in the province that achieved a dismal zero % pass rate and this year, the department was hoping that this would not be the case. 
Dlungwane visited several schools in Umlazi Township and Ndwedwe area to check on the progress of the exams.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

 







