  Acting head of Curriculum Dr Barney Mthembu addresses a briefing at the Vukuzakhe High school in Umlazi where more than 200 learnet from schools were in the Ngonyameni area have been placed. The student were moved from Ngonyameni because of protest over service delivery Video: Thami Magubane
 


He visited Vukuzakhe High School in Umlazi where more than 200 pupils from four schools were being accommodated after their schools were damaged during service delivery protests in Ngonyameni.
“We have done all to make sure the pupils do well, through winter classes, camps and Saturday classes. Last  year we had three schools that achieved zero % and the aim is to eliminate those schools. We also want to decrease the number of schools that achieved less than 60%," he said.

